										<p id='intelliTxt' class="intro">Green fees too expensive?  Golf course too far away?  Introducing tennis ball golf (&quot;tolf&quot;), an incredibly fun, challenging, and FREE way to spend an afternoon with friends!  Golf skills not necessary.</p>
									</div>
								
					<!-- google_ad_section_end() -->

				
<section class="Module body FLC">
			<dl class="difficulty">
			<dt>Difficulty:</dt>
			<dd>Moderately Easy</dd>
		</dl>
			<h2 class="Underline sectionTitle Heading2"><span class="line">Instructions</span></h2>
	
    <section>
		<!-- google_ad_section_start() -->
					<section class="thingsYouNeed">
				<div class="tape"></div>
				<div class="container">
					<header>
						<h4 class="header Heading5"><span>things you'll need:</span></h4>
					</header>
					<ul class="UnorderedTitleList">
												<li><span class="title">one 7-iron golf club per person</span></li>
												<li><span class="title">one tennis ball per person</span></li>
												<li><span class="title">creativity</span></li>
											</ul>
				</div>
			</section>
		
		<ol id="intelliTxt" class="steps">
						<li class="section">
								<ul>
								<li class="step">
															<span class="stepNumber">1</span>
														<div class="stepMeat">
																	<a href="http://i.ehow.co.uk/images/a05/6t/nm/play-tolf-official-guide-1.1-800X800.jpg" class="Thumbnail" data-type="modal" data-modal-content="7-iron: The Official Tolf Club">
										<img src="http://v5-ui.ehowcdn.com/ui/shared/images/pixel.gif" width="98" height="73" data-img="http://img.ehow.com/article-preview/ehow-uk/images/a05/6t/nm/play-tolf-official-guide-1.1-800x800.jpg" />																					<span class="Note caption">7-iron: The Official Tolf Club</span>
																													</a>
																<div itemprop="step"><p>Each tolfer needs a 7-iron golf club (the &quot;official&quot; club of tolf) and a tennis ball.</p></div>
							</div>
						</li>
										<li class="step">
															<span class="stepNumber">2</span>
														<div class="stepMeat">
																	<a href="http://i.ehow.co.uk/images/a05/6t/nm/play-tolf-official-guide-1.2-800X800.jpg" class="Thumbnail" data-type="modal" data-modal-content="Choose an area with lots of potential tolf holes.">
										<img src="http://v5-ui.ehowcdn.com/ui/shared/images/pixel.gif" width="98" height="73" data-img="http://img.ehow.com/article-preview/ehow-uk/images/a05/6t/nm/play-tolf-official-guide-1.2-800x800.jpg" />																					<span class="Note caption">Choose an area with lots of potential tolf holes.</span>
																													</a>
																<div itemprop="step"><p>Choose an area in which to tolf.  The area should be spacious and, unlike a regular golf course, filled with obstacles - potential &quot;holes.&quot;  (See &quot;Tips&quot; for ideas on holes.)</p></div>
							</div>
						</li>
										<li class="step">
															<span class="stepNumber">3</span>
														<div class="stepMeat">
																<div itemprop="step"><p>Choose your first &quot;hole,&quot; and choose a par for it.  When choosing the par for a hole, you'll want to consider several factors:<br />
- the distance from the starting point (or &quot;tee&quot;)<br />
- the difficulty of the terrain (e.g. balls roll farther on cement than grass)<br />
- the size of the hole itself (e.g. a wall is easier to hit than a light pole), and<br />
- the skill level of the tolfers.<br />
Pars usually range from 3-5, with 3 being the easiest or shortest, and 5 being the longest or hardest.</p></div>
							</div>
						</li>
										<li class="step">
															<span class="stepNumber">4</span>
														<div class="stepMeat">
																<div itemprop="step"><p>Tee up!  Keep track of the amount of strokes it takes you to get the ball to the hole.</p></div>
							</div>
						</li>
										<li class="step">
															<span class="stepNumber">5</span>
														<div class="stepMeat">
																	<a href="http://i.ehow.co.uk/images/a05/6t/nm/play-tolf-official-guide-1.5-800X800.jpg" class="Thumbnail" data-type="modal" data-modal-content="A &#039;Flip Shot&#039; gives the tolfer more control over the loft of the ball on short-range shots.">
										<img src="http://v5-ui.ehowcdn.com/ui/shared/images/pixel.gif" width="98" height="73" data-img="http://img.ehow.com/article-preview/ehow-uk/images/a05/6t/nm/play-tolf-official-guide-1.5-800x800.jpg" />																					<span class="Note caption">A 'Flip Shot' gives the tolfer more control over the loft of the ball on short-range shots.</span>
																													</a>
																<div itemprop="step"><p>The basic rules are as follows:</p>

<p>1)   Score is kept in the same way as in golf.  So, if it takes you 8 strokes to reach the hole on a par 4, your score is +4.  Obviously, the lower your score, the better.</p>

<p>2)   In general, the highest number of strokes a tolfer may receive on a single hole is 10.</p>

<p>3)   If a tolfer hits a non-tolfing person from the tee shot, the tolfer receives an automatic hole-in-one!</p>

<p>4)   &quot;Flip shots&quot; are allowed and encouraged - the tolfer need not take a full swing to take a shot.</p>

<p>5)   &quot;Advanced&quot; rules may be added, or may replace these general rules.</p></div>
							</div>
						</li>
										<li class="step">
															<span class="stepNumber">6</span>
														<div class="stepMeat">
																	<a href="http://i.ehow.co.uk/images/a05/6t/nm/play-tolf-official-guide-1.6-800X800.jpg" class="Thumbnail" data-type="modal" data-modal-content="You can move a ball when necessary, but not closer to the hole.">
										<img src="http://v5-ui.ehowcdn.com/ui/shared/images/pixel.gif" width="98" height="73" data-img="http://img.ehow.com/article-preview/ehow-uk/images/a05/6t/nm/play-tolf-official-guide-1.6-800x800.jpg" />																					<span class="Note caption">You can move a ball when necessary, but not closer to the hole.</span>
																													</a>
																<div itemprop="step"><p>If the ball comes to rest in a place where it can't be hit (like a bush or very tall grass), the tolfer can move the ball to a hittable location without penalty.  He cannot move it closer to the hole though.</p></div>
							</div>
						</li>
										<li class="step">
															<span class="stepNumber">7</span>
														<div class="stepMeat">
																<div itemprop="step"><p>&quot;Advanced&quot; rules can be serious or goofy, but are always fun!</p>

<p>1)   &quot;PGA Style&quot; - unhittable balls can only be moved with a 1-stroke penalty, and there is no 10-stroke limit on holes.</p>

<p>2)   &quot;Drop 'em&quot; - if the ball lands behind the spot from which it was hit (by bouncing off a tree, for example), the tolfer must hit his next shot with his pants below his knees!  May not be appropriate for mixed company....</p>

<p>3)   &quot;Target Practice&quot; - hitting someone with the tolf ball on any shot - not just the tee shot - counts as a hole-in-one.</p>

<p>4)   &quot;Replace Your Divot&quot; - if a tolfer creates a divot, another tolfer may throw it at him.</p></div>
							</div>
						</li>
									</ul>
						</li>
					</ol>
	</section>
	<!-- google_ad_section_end() -->

	
	</section>

